{
  "text": "Western Blotting-Treated cells were collected and lysed as described previously [CITATION_1] . Protein samples (10 g/lane) were subjected to SDS-PAGE and transferred to PVDF membranes using the iBlot Gel Transfer system (Invitrogen). The membranes were blocked, incubated with primary antibody, washed, and incubated with the secondary HRP-labeled antibody. Bands were visualized with the ECL Prime Western blotting Detection System (GE Healthcare) and LAS-3000 (Fujifilm, Tokyo, Japan). A densitometric analysis of blotted membranes was performed using ImageJ software.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "26906068"
